Key Match Events: Dominik Szoboszlai received a great low pass from Zsolt Nagy and scored in the 38th minute.
Dominik Szoboszlai converted a penalty kick in the second half, making it 2-0.
Edin Džeko had a couple of shots on goal but was stopped by the Hungarian goalkeeper Dénes Dibusz.
Post-Match Reflections: Dominik Szoboszlai praised for his 14th goal in 49 games for Hungary.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Hungary beat Bosnia and Herzegovina 2-0 on the road in Zenica.
